# 2009-11-27.jmd.1: YafaRay as associated project

This resolution was adopted by the Board of Directors of SPI at their
meeting of [December 9, 2009](/meetings/minutes/2009/2009-12-09/).

### WHEREAS

1. YafaRay is a substantial and useful open source project.

2. YafaRay would like SPI's support and assistance, including taking
   donations.


### THE SPI BOARD RESOLVES THAT

1. YafaRay is formally invited to become an SPI
   Associated Project, according to the SPI Framework for Associated
   Projects, SPI Resolution 1998-11-16.iwj.1-amended-2004-08-10.iwj.1, a
   copy of which can be found at
   [http://www.spi-inc.org/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1](/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1/)

2. Currently, Alvaro Luna Bautista is recognised by SPI as the current
   authoritative decision maker and SPI liaison for YafaRay. Successors
   will be appointed by the YafaRay Team, as listed on
   [http://www.yafaray.org/about](http://www.yafaray.org/about)

3. This invitation will lapse, if not accepted, 60 days after it is
   approved by the SPI Board.


